President Barack Obama congratulated Macky Sall on his victory in Senegal's presidential elections, stating that the election was transparent and reflected the will of the Senegalese people. He also praised President Abdoulaye Wade for his leadership and friendship to the United States. President Obama expressed his desire to build productive ties with President-elect Sall and deepen the bonds between the United States and Senegal. He commended Senegal for being a leading example of good governance and democracy in Africa and emphasized the importance of peaceful and democratic elections in countering non-democratic forces. President Obama expressed hope that Africa's democratic wave would continue and affirmed the United States' commitment to maintaining a strong partnership with Senegal to strengthen democracy, peace, and prosperity in the region.